            },
            "answer_text": "HIV virus is present in all body fluids of the body of HIV-positive people. But all the liquids of the human body do not have the same power of transmission. The virus is too small in saliva, sweat, tears, vomit or urine to be transmitted. On the other hand, blood, sperm, seminal fluid (clear liquid that flows at the beginning of erection), vaginal secretions, rectal fluid and breast milk can transmit HIV. ",
            "date": "Answered December 13, 2018",
